{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide vote based on record. Evaluate. The proposition: By May 8, 2026, a message or note credibly reported to have been written by Jeffrey Epstein and intended as a suicide note, final message, or equivalent communication had been made publicly available.\n\nWe have evidence: official order unsealing note described as \"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\". Multiple credible outlets reported that. They also note lack of authentication, but the rule only requires \"credibly reported\". The reports are credible and describe note as suicide note. They also describe intent via language. So preponderance likely met.\n\nDefense argues not enough because not authenticated, but rule doesn't require authentication. So we should vote demonstrated.\n\nProvide concise rationale <=3 sentences.\n\nNow submit vote.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b65b7070b328616f","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782796207510,"responseId":"gen-1782796207-siTU67UW9diJ0MfZywDR"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide vote based on record. Evaluate. The proposition: By May 8, 2026, a message or note credibly reported to have been written by Jeffrey Epstein and intended as a suicide note, final message, or equivalent communication had been made publicly available.\n\nWe have evidence: official order unsealing note described as \"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\". Multiple credible outlets reported that. They also note lack of authentication, but the rule only requires \"credibly reported\". The reports are credible and describe note as suicide note. They also describe intent via language. So preponderance likely met.\n\nDefense argues not enough because not authenticated, but rule doesn't require authentication. So we should vote demonstrated.\n\nProvide concise rationale <=3 sentences.\n\nNow submit vote.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b65b7070b328616f","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782796207510,"responseId":"gen-1782796207-siTU67UW9diJ0MfZywDR"}}
